 1994 and later released on The Bends , is about the song. Expand      +444     6  4   Share    Q&A Find answers to frequently asked questions about the song and explore its deeper meaning Ask a question What did Radiohead say about "Creep"?  Genius Answer 2 contributors Thom Yorke said that the song is trying:  to assert a sexual persona and on the other hand trying desperately to negate it.  Explaining why it’s rarely played at their live shows, Yorke said that:  It can be cool sometimes, but other times I want to stop halfway through and be like, ‘Nah, this isn’t happening’.  Who produced “Creep” by Radiohead?  When did Radiohead release “Creep”?  Who wrote “Creep” by Radiohead?     Pablo Honey (Collectors Edition)    (2009) Radiohead 1. You 2. Creep 3. How Do You? 4. Stop Whispering 5. Thinking About You 6. Anyone Can Play Guitar 7. Ripcord 8. Vegetable 9. Prove Yourself 10. I Can’t 11. Lurgee 12. Blow Out 13. Prove Yourself (Drill Version) 14. Stupid Car 15. You (Drill Version) 16. Thinking About You (Drill Version) 17. Inside My Head 18. Million Dollar Question 19. Yes I Am 20. Blow Out (Remix) 21. Inside My Head (Live) 22. Creep (Acoustic) 23. Vegetable (Live)  (Missing Lyrics) 24. Killer Cars (Live) 25. Faithless the Wonderboy 26. Coke Babies 27. Pop Is Dead 28. Banana Co. (Acoustic)  (Missing Lyrics) 29. Ripcord (Live)  (Missing Lyrics) 30. Stop Whispering (U.S. Version)  (Missing Lyrics) 31. Prove Yourself (BBC Radio 1 Evening Session)  (Missing Lyrics) 32. Creep (BBC Radio 1 Evening Session) 33. I Can’t (BBC Radio 1 Evening Session)  (Missing Lyrics) 34. Nothing Touches Me (BBC Radio 1 Evening Session) Expand      Credits Producer Chris Hufford Writers Thom Yorke , Jonny Greenwood , Ed O’Brien , Colin Greenwood , Philip Selway , Albert Hammond & Mike Hazlewood Mastering Engineer Paul Q. Kolderie & Sean Slade Mixing Engineer Chris Blair Phonographic Copyright ℗ XL Recordings Copyright © XL Recordings Distributor Beggars Group Publisher Warner/Chappell Guit